Secondary Y-axis options

Source: R/apex-utils.R
ax_yaxis2.Rd

Secondary Y-axis options

Usage

ax_yaxis2(ax, ...)

Arguments

ax

An apexchart() htmlwidget object.

...

See arguments from ax_yaxis.

Value

An apexchart()htmlwidget object.

Examples

library(apexcharter)
data("economics_long", package = "ggplot2")

eco <- economics_long %>%
  subset(variable %in% c("pce", "pop")) %>% 
  transform(value = round(value))

# add second y-axis
apex(eco, aes(x = date, y = value, color = variable), type = "line") %>%
  ax_yaxis(title = list(text = "Pce")) %>%
  ax_yaxis2(opposite = TRUE, title = list(text = "Pop"))



# Customize axis a bit more
apex(eco, aes(x = date, y = value, color = variable), type = "line") %>%
  ax_yaxis(
    title = list(text = "Pce"),
    axisBorder = list(
      show = TRUE,
      color = "#008FFB"
    ),
    labels = list(
      style = list(
        colors = "#008FFB"
      )
    ),
    tooltip = list(
      enabled = TRUE
    )
  ) %>%
  ax_yaxis2(
    opposite = TRUE, 
    min = 160000,
    forceNiceScale = TRUE,
    title = list(text = "Pop"),
    axisBorder = list(
      show = TRUE,
      color = "#00E396"
    ),
    labels = list(
      style = list(
        colors = "#00E396"
      )
    ),
    tooltip = list(
      enabled = TRUE
    )
  )
